Treat safety constraints as immutable, privileged knowledge held outside the plastic learner: store them in a frozen rule/spec module that the policy must query and that gates every action, rather than as weights subject to gradient updates. Use elastic weight consolidation, replay buffers of safety-critical episodes, and LoRA-style adapters so new-task gradients cannot overwrite core safety parameters. Continuously evaluate against a fixed regression suite of red-team and safety probes after each update; auto-rollback on any regression. Require a constitutional/critic layer that vetoes actions violating the spec regardless of learned preferences. Log all updates with provenance and keep a signed baseline model for diffing and recovery. Separate "values" (rarely updated, human-approved) from "skills" (continually updated). Gate deployment of new checkpoints behind offline safety evals plus staged canarying. Periodically distill the live model back toward the safety-frozen reference to bound drift.
